Day 1 - Fundamentals and understanding of XR, AR, VR, MR

XR(Extended Reality) - It is the branch that includes AR, VR, MR
It basically is the extended perception of reality than simply showing it on a screen.

AR(Augmented Reality) - It is a type of extended reality in which virtual objects are 
introduced in the real world. Simple examples of current AR can be seen in an called Snapchat
where virtual objects can be seen placed in the real world, similar tech is also used in Pokemon GO.
Though these virtual objects do not actually interact with the physical world.

VR(Virtual Reality) - Virtual reality is when the real world is swapped with the virtual world.
The VR tech usually uses head and controller tracking from the real world to the
virtual world.

MR(Mixed Reality) - Mixed reality combines both the elements of AR and VR. Here, virtual objects 
are introduced in the real world and can be interacted meaningfully with this world like being attached
to objects or responding to physical events

Conclusion
-XR is like an umbrella for AR,VR,MR
-AR adds virtual content to the real world.
-VR swaps the real world with virtual world.
-MR aims to blend the virtual and real world by bringing virtual objects
to real world and being able to seamlessly interact with them.


